                            <comment id="13284534" author="giles7777" created="Mon, 28 May 2012 20:04:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking around I see that HornetQ has a REST api as well.  They return the JMS property values as headers.  This looks reasonable to me and shouldn&apos;t break any existing clients using this api.  I&apos;ll attach a proposed change to support this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13284538" author="giles7777" created="Mon, 28 May 2012 20:12:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for including JMS properties into the response headers.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
